---
// NextHop — Terms of Service. Astro 5, pure SSG, no client-side JS.
const title = "Terms of Service — NextHop";
const description = "The terms that govern your use of the NextHop travel-planning app.";
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#D4A015" />
  <title>{title}</title>
  <meta name="description" content={description} />
  <meta property="og:title" content="Terms of Service — NextHop" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="The terms that govern your use of the NextHop travel-planning app." />
  <meta property="og:image" content="/nexthop-og.png" />
  <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --gold: #D4A015;
      --gold-deep: #B8860B;
      --bg: #FAF7F2;
      --ink: #1A1A1A;
      --muted: #4A4A4A;
      --card: #FFFFFF;
      --hairline: #ECE6DA;
      --sans: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    html { -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: var(--sans);
      line-height: 1.68;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
    }

    .site-header {
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
      background: rgba(250, 247, 242, 0.85);
      backdrop-filter: saturate(160%) blur(8px);
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 10;
    }
    .site-header .inner {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 16px 24px;
    }
    .brand {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 11px;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    .brand-globe {
      width: 29px;
      height: 29px;
      flex: none;
    }
    .brand span {
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    main {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: clamp(40px, 8vw, 72px) 24px 24px;
    }
    .doc-title {
      font-size: clamp(34px, 8vw, 46px);
      line-height: 1.05;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .effective {
      margin: 12px 0 0;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold-deep);
    }
    .rule {
      height: 3px;
      width: 56px;
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 2px;
      margin: 28px 0 0;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--gold) 0%, var(--gold-deep) 100%);
    }
    .content { margin-top: 8px; }
    .content h2 {
      font-size: clamp(20px, 5vw, 24px);
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 44px 0 0;
    }
    .content p {
      margin: 14px 0 0;
      font-size: 17px;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-wrap: pretty;
    }
    .content p strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }
    .content a { color: var(--gold-deep); font-weight: 600; text-underline-offset: 3px; }

    .closing {
      margin-top: 52px;
      padding-top: 28px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
      font-size: 17px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .closing a { color: var(--gold-deep); font-weight: 600; text-underline-offset: 3px; }

    footer {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 32px 24px 64px;
    }
    .back {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .back:hover { color: var(--gold-deep); }

    a:focus-visible {
      outline: 2px solid var(--gold);
      outline-offset: 3px;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    @media print {
      :root { --bg: #fff; }
      body { background: #fff; line-height: 1.5; }
      .site-header { position: static; border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc; background: #fff; backdrop-filter: none; }
      main, footer { max-width: 100%; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; }
      .content h2 { margin-top: 22px; page-break-after: avoid; }
      .content p { color: #222; font-size: 11.5pt; }
      .rule { background: #999; }
      .effective, .doc-title, .brand span { color: #000; }
      .back, .site-header { display: none; }
      a { color: #000; text-decoration: underline; }
      @page { margin: 18mm; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header class="site-header">
    <div class="inner">
      <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="NextHop — back to home">
        <svg class="brand-globe" viewBox="-31 -31 724 724" aria-hidden="true">
          <defs>
            <clipPath id="brandGlobeClip"><circle cx="331" cy="331" r="320"></circle></clipPath>
          </defs>
          <g clip-path="url(#brandGlobeClip)" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="50" fill="none">
            <line x1="0" y1="331" x2="662" y2="331"></line>
            <ellipse cx="331" cy="331" rx="160" ry="320"></ellipse>
          </g>
          <circle cx="331" cy="331" r="320" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="50"></circle>
        </svg>
        <span>NextHop</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <h1 class="doc-title">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="effective">Effective May 28, 2026</p>
    <hr class="rule" />

    <div class="content">
      <h2>Acceptance of these terms</h2>
      <p>By downloading, signing into, or otherwise using NextHop you agree to these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, please do not use the app.</p>

      <h2>What NextHop does</h2>
      <p>NextHop is a travel-planning app. It helps you discover places, build day-by-day itineraries, save favourites, and view curated travel content. Suggestions and itineraries are generated to inspire your trip — they are not professional travel advice. Always verify opening hours, prices, and bookings before relying on them.</p>

      <h2>Your account</h2>
      <p>You are responsible for the accuracy of the information you provide and for keeping your password and device secure. You must be at least 13 years old to create an account. You may close your account at any time by emailing <a href="mailto:hello@nexthopapp.com">hello@nexthopapp.com</a>; we may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms or applicable law.</p>

      <h2>Subscriptions and payments</h2>
      <p>NextHop offers an optional Pro subscription with monthly and annual billing tiers. Payment is charged to your Apple ID account at confirmation of purchase. Subscriptions renew automatically at the price shown in-app at the time of renewal unless you cancel at least 24 hours before the end of the current period. You can manage or cancel subscriptions in your Apple ID settings; deleting the app does not cancel the subscription. Refunds, where applicable, are handled by Apple under the App Store refund policy.</p>

      <h2>Free trial and free features</h2>
      <p>Free users may create one trip and save a limited number of favourites. Where a free trial of Pro is offered, any unused portion of the trial period is forfeited when you purchase Pro before the trial ends.</p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You may not use NextHop to violate any law, infringe anyone's rights, attempt to gain unauthorised access to our systems, reverse-engineer the app, or interfere with other users. You agree not to upload content that is illegal, infringing, harassing, or that you do not have the right to share. We may remove content and suspend accounts that breach this section.</p>

      <h2>Content and intellectual property</h2>
      <p>NextHop, its name, the wireframe globe mark, the curated itinerary content, and the app's design are owned by NextHop and protected by intellectual-property laws. You receive a personal, non-transferable, non-exclusive licence to use the app for your own travel planning. Imagery shown in the app comes from sources such as Pexels and Unsplash and is used under their respective licences; we credit photographers where required.</p>

      <h2>Third-party content and links</h2>
      <p>NextHop displays content from third parties (e.g. maps, restaurant names, place descriptions). We do not control, endorse, or guarantee any third-party content. Following an external link or opening an external service is at your own risk.</p>

      <h2>Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>NextHop is provided "as is" and "as available". To the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, express or implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not guarantee the availability, accuracy, completeness, or timeliness of any place data, opening hours, prices, transport timings, or weather information shown.</p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, NextHop and its team will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits, data, use, or goodwill arising from your use of the app. Our total liability for any claim related to NextHop will not exceed the amount you paid us in the 12 months before the claim arose, or USD 50 if you paid nothing.</p>

      <h2>Changes to the app and these terms</h2>
      <p>We may add, change, or discontinue features at any time, and may update these terms by posting an updated version in the app with a new effective date. When changes are material we will surface a notice in the app. Continued use after an update means you accept the new terms.</p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>These terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which NextHop's operating entity is registered, without regard to conflict-of-law rules. Any dispute will be resolved in the courts of that jurisdiction, unless a mandatory consumer protection law requires otherwise.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about these terms? Email <a href="mailto:hello@nexthopapp.com">hello@nexthopapp.com</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="closing">That's everything. Head back to <a href="/">NextHop</a>.</p>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <a class="back" href="/">← Back to NextHop</a>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
